      <h1 class="blog-title">Getting Started with Legacy Odyssey</h1>

      <p class="blog-meta">Getting Started &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; 3 min read</p>

      <div class="blog-body">

        <p>Here's exactly what happens when you sign up.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>What you get</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>Your child's own .com domain — registered automatically at checkout</li>
          <li>Access to the web editor at legacyodyssey.com/account</li>
          <li>The iOS app (free download)</li>
          <li>The Android app (free download)</li>
          <li>The book website, live from day one</li>
          <li>Password protection for the site</li>
          <li>All sections of the book</li>
        </ul>

        <p>The domain registration is automatic. You pick the name at checkout, availability is checked, and if it's open, it's registered and connected to your book.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Two ways to edit</h2>

        <p><strong>The app</strong> — Download on iOS or Android. Sign in with the email and password from checkout. The dashboard shows every section as a grid. Tap any card to start filling it in.</p>

        <p><strong>The web editor</strong> — Sign in at legacyodyssey.com/account from any browser. Same sections, same fields. Most people find the web editor easier for longer writing, the app more convenient for adding photos on the go.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Your domain and when it goes live</h2>

        <p>At checkout you pick your child's domain name. We register it automatically — there's nothing you need to do. But there's a short window after purchase where the domain isn't accessible yet.</p>

        <p>Here's why: when a new domain is registered, its DNS records (the instructions that tell the internet where to send visitors) need time to spread across global servers. It's like a new address being added to a postal directory — it takes a little while before everyone has the updated list.</p>

        <p>In most cases your site is live within <strong>15 minutes</strong> of purchase. While you wait, Legacy Odyssey checks your domain automatically every 5 minutes in the background. The moment it confirms your site is up, you'll get a second email — <strong>"Your site is live!"</strong> — with your URL and your book password ready to share with family.</p>

        <p>You don't need to wait for any of this. The app and the web editor are fully available the moment you sign in. Start filling in your child's book right away — everything you add will be there when the domain comes live.</p>

        <h2>Sharing with family</h2>

        <p>Once you get the "Your site is live!" email, your book is at your-childs-name.com. Share the URL and the book password with whoever you want access. They open it in any browser — no account needed on their end.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>See it first</h2>

        <p>The demo is at <a href="https://www.your-childs-name.com">your-childs-name.com</a> — password is <strong>legacy</strong>. It shows what a complete book looks like from a visitor's perspective.</p>

        <div class="blog-cta-box">
          <p><strong>Your child's own .com, their own book.</strong></p>
          <a href="/#pricing" class="btn-primary">Get Started &rarr;</a>
        </div>

